{
  "_comment": "Example policy definition — role_policy type. Each rule maps a single action to the set of roles permitted to perform it. Evaluation uses deny-overrides: if any rule denies, the request is denied; if any rule allows and none deny, the request is allowed; if no rule covers the action, the default is deny. This is the serialized form of RolePolicyRule from basis_core.policy.rules.",
  "policy_id": "basis-core-default-role-policy",
  "policy_type": "role_policy",
  "version": "v1.1.0",
  "evaluation_semantics": "deny_overrides",
  "description": "Default role-based access policy for a single-zone BASIS deployment. Viewer may read; operator may read and write control actions; admin may do everything including audit log access.",
  "created_at": "2026-05-22T00:00:00Z",
  "created_by": "system",
  "rules": [
